 <!-- Introduction -->
 <!-- The introduction should start as shown: -->
 <purpose>
   <p>
     This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module to record:</p>
<ul>
<li>a schematic drawing;</li>
<li> links between the elements of a schematic drawing and the things that they
stand for;</li>
<li>a symbol library;</li>
<li>definition of a drawing revision or a drawing sheet revision as a class of
document.</li>
</ul>
 </purpose>

 <!-- Items in scope -->
 <inscope>
<li><p>the definition of a schematic drawing, including the definition of the
elements of the drawing, their composition and connectivity;</p>
<note number="1">This capability is provided by the referenced <module_ref linkend="schematic_drawing:1_scope">Schematic_drawing</module_ref> application
module.</note>
</li>
<li><p>the definition of a library of symbols;</p>
<note number="2">This capability is provided by the referenced <module_ref linkend="schematic_element_library:1_scope">Schematic_element_library</module_ref> application
module.</note>
</li>
<li><p>the association between an element of a schematic drawing and the thing that is symbolized;</p>
<note number="3">This capability is provided by the referenced <module_ref linkend="symbolization_by_schematic_element:1_scope">Symbolization_by_schematic_element</module_ref> application
module.</note>
</li>
<li><p>the definition of a class of document that is a drawing revision or a
drawing sheet revision.</p>
</li>
 </inscope>

 <!-- Items out of scope -->
 <outscope>
<li><p>the nature of the objects that are presented on a schematic drawing.</p>
<note number="4">The functional nature of the objects that are presented
on a schematic drawing is specified by the
<module_ref linkend="functional_data:1_scope">Functional_data</module_ref>
application module. </note>
</li>
 </outscope>

